The paper discusses a technique for improving the performance of Binary Neural Networks (BNNs), which are commonly used in machine learning for their compute cost reduction and memory savings. The paper focuses on addressing the gradient mismatch problem in BNNs, which is a common issue that affects their performance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY).
